text: Yesterday, Thursday, 08 September 2022 was my second time going to MD6 - Centre for Translational Medicine, having volunteered as a recovered patient to be interviewed by future medical students whom my attending psychiatrist is their professor and lecturer. In hope of facilitating others who may be first time going to MD6 - Centre for Translational Medicine, I have attached 3 photos that I have taken respectively yesterday after my interview session.
great building except the lift is always under maintenance

Courteous security staff mans the front desk here and registers visitors. They find out your purpose of visit and remotely unlocks the door to the lift lobby for you.

As a general member of public, if you need to call on this place, more likely than not, it is to participate in some form of research study.
Facilities available. The place is a clean, open environment. The service area is available in the basement.
One of medical research centre of NUS/NUH to further develop research into medicine.
